Excessive requirements for applications for public procurement will be excluded by law
The legislation may establish exhaustive requirements for applications for participation in procurement.
In the autumn session at the plenary session, the State Duma plan to consider in the second reading a bill that establishes requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the procurement, the participants of which can only be small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities."
The bill was developed in pursuance of a roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the Development of Small and Medium-Sized Entrepreneurship in the Russian Federation until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to require as part of the application from the participants of the procurement - small and medium-sized businesses.
And also a list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by certain types of legal entities" framework regulates the procurement activities of certain types of legal entities.
Requirements for the content, form, execution and composition of the application for participation in the procurement are established by customers independently in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, customers establish redundant requirements for the content, execution of the application, the mandatory presence of certificates, certificates, statements, the period of receipt of which in the authorized bodies is comparable to the deadline for submission of applications, which leads to the impossibility of participation in such a purchase and a decrease in the number of participants in the procurement," - stated in the explanation to the bill.
The new bill provides for the establishment of an exhaustive list of documents that customers have the right to require as part of the application from procurement participants who are small and medium-sized businesses.
"The adoption of the document will allow to exclude the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are small and medium-sized businesses," - stated in the explanatory note.
