Degtyarev was surprised by the information about the purchase of gas "Sakhalin-1" for dollars
Acting Governor of the Khabarovsk Territory Mikhail Degtyarev on Sunday, July 26, during a meeting with residents of the Soviet Harbour was surprised that the region is buying Sakhalin gas produced by the American company Exxon Neftegas, for dollars.
U.S. gas contracted in dollars until 2025.
"I'm honest, I didn't know that, and I'm in such a knockdown because of this information.
I did not even have an idea that this is still possible in 2020 in Russia," - quotes him "RIA Novosti."
Degtyarev noted that this issue was discussed with the head of the Ministry of Energy of Russia Alexander Novak during his visit to Khabarovsk on July 24.
The acting governor also stressed that by 2025, Gazprom is switching to supply Russian CHP and capacity, which means that Russian gas purchased in rubles "at normal prices" will be used.
The Sakhalin-1 project is being implemented through a production sharing agreement, where the project operator with a share of 30% is Exxon Neftegas Ltd, another 20% at Rosneft, Japanese Sodeco 30% and Indian ONGC 20%.
Khabarovsk region has been acquiring gas from this project since 2005.
