The actor of the Russian series responded to accusations of "propaganda of LGBT and feminism"
The actor of the Russian series "Chiki," the creator of which was accused of "propaganda of LGBT and feminism," responded to the claims to the film.
The authors "understand the sharpness of the raised topics and did not want to offend anyone," said American Stephen Thomas Oxner in an interview with the publication "Rise."
"I think it's a story about the power and general aspects of human life.
This has nothing to do with LGBT and feminism," said the actor, who played the father of a boy who dressed in women's clothes.
He stressed that he was "proud of work" and does not consider it propaganda.
At the same time, the American added, he is frightened by the reaction of some people to the storyline of the series: for example, there was a case when "a man in a deep bout shot the set and said that all this is not true."
"Then a couple of cases were when we met disgruntled locals who didn't understand what we were doing.
But we were open, so the people who first came with the claims, began to help us," - he concluded.
The case of the shooting, explains the publication, occurred in September 2019 in Kabardino-Balkaria: a drunken man attacked the car of the crew with a weapon, after which he was detained by police officers.
Earlier it was reported that the public ombudsman for the protection of the family Olga Baranets sent a complaint to the Ministry of Internal Affairs and Roskomnadzor on the service more.tv, which posted the Russian TV series "Chiki."
Baranets accused the creators of the series of "propaganda of non-traditional sexual relations and feminism," paying attention to the fact that the main characters of the film work prostitutes, and the series contains "scenes of physical and psychological violence."
The ombudsman was also outraged by the fact that "the series pays much attention to homosexual sexual orientation" of the minor character.
The comedy drama "Chicki" tells about three prostitutes who started a new life and opened a business on the advice of a friend.
