The woman threw the body of her husband in a pit and poured concrete near Belgorod
In the Belgorod region, a woman confessed to the murder of her own husband, whom she dumped into a pit with waste and poured concrete, according to the website of the regional administration of the Investigative Committee of the Russian Federation.
The suspect has been married to the man since 1999.
In recent years, the husband began to abuse alcohol and after another quarrel, the woman decided to kill.
"When the husband fell asleep, the suspect tied his arms and legs, put a plastic bag on his head and crushed him with a pillow.
When the spouse stopped filing signs of life, wrapped the body in the carpet, carried out into the yard and hid in the cesspool.
The next day, she called the concrete mixer and poured the pit with concrete," the management said.
The woman later reported that the husband was missing.
Relatives of the deceased appealed to the police, which opened the pit and extracted the body.
The investigation intends to ask the court for the arrest of the suspect.
The investigation of the criminal case is ongoing.
